.TH DTS 1 "February 2026" "dts" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
dts \- print UTC timestamps in multiple formats
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B dts
[\fIOPTIONS\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B dts
prints the current UTC timestamp.

By default, output is ISO-8601 style with millisecond precision:

YYYY-MM-DDTHH:MM:SS.mmmZ
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-f, \-\-file
Print a filename-safe timestamp format:
YYYY-MM-DDTHH-MM-SSZ
.TP
.B \-s, \-\-seconds
Print second precision format:
YYYY-MM-DDTHH:MM:SSZ
.TP
.B \-h, \-\-help
Show help text and exit.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success.
.TP
.B 2
Invalid arguments or conflicting options.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Default output:
.B dts
.TP
Second precision:
.B dts \-s
.TP
Filename-safe output:
.B dts \-f
.SH AUTHOR
Alex Atkinson and contributors.
